                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d409">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4287: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1"
                            type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-19T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 19, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 19—3 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>75. My telegram No. 69, February 18, 3 p.m.<note n="65" xml:id="d409fn65">Not
                        printed.</note> I learn from Japanese general that last night Japanese
                    military commander sent to Chinese military commander demands for withdrawal
                    with time limit. Press agencies this morning publish demands which are similar
                    to those told me yesterday by Japanese Consul General and reported in my
                    telegram. Japanese Consulate General states news agencies reports substantially
                    correct and one translation will be ready by 3 o’clock this afternoon.</p>
                <p>Repeated to the Legation and Nanking for information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CES1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
